    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-09-25</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-12-19T19:16:58Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Federal Agency Program Realignment and Closure Act - Establishes the Federal Agency Program Realignment and Closure Commission to: (1) evaluate each executive agency and its programs; and (2) submit to the President and Congress a list of the agencies and programs it recommends eliminating or realigning.</p><p>Requires the Commission to recommend that an agency or program be: (1) realigned where a function performed by two or more agencies or programs can be consolidated; (2) eliminated if it performs a function that is also provided by a state or that would be more efficient if performed at the state level; or (3) eliminated if it performs a function that can be more efficently performed by a private entity.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
